Show HN: Zefy – An advanced bookmarking app to organize and collaborate on links
text:
We have been working on this for a few weeks - would love to get your feedback.

Information is generally spread across various apps and sites, and we wanted an easy way to organize and manage them. We also built sharing and comment features because we realized how crucial they are when collaborating with people on some project. The app is in active development and the idea is to make it super-easy to store, manage and collaborate on information.

Here is a quick demo: https://www.loom.com/share/b862b40baebd4b6cba261422a6fc0813

Show HN: I built developer tooling for the Airtable API that I needed
text:
As a software engineer, I've experienced firsthand the challenges of working with the Airtable API.

As more non-technical users began using the platform in our growing business, the need for engineering to automate processes and sync data into Airtable grew. However, keeping track of process failures and ensuring that no unresolved failures slipped by was difficult and required significant effort.

That's why I created Airwalker, a toolkit that improves the reliability of processes using the Airtable API and helps you correct issues quickly and with minimal effort.

Here are some of the features Airwalker offers:

* Base schema timeline

* Request/response logging

* Edit & replay

* Custom automatically maintained TypeScript types

Airwalker is free to use right now, and I welcome any feedback or suggestions.

Ask HN: Official Hacker News ranking experiments?
text:
Recently, we published a problem analsysis and our approach to improve the HN ranking algorithm: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=35183317

As a follow-up, we'd like to ask if the community is interested in official experiments with approaches like this. We'd suggest having a second, experimental front-page on HN, which applies the upoteRate metric to the HN formula, as described here: https://github.com/social-protocols/news#a-proposed-new-formula

To get a feeling how stories with a high upvoteRate look like, we prepared a page, where all frontpage stories are sorted by upvoteRate: https://news.social-protocols.org/best-upvoterate.

What do you think?
